Key Match Events: Dala opened the scoring after 38 minutes
Namibia defender Lubeni Haukongo received a red card shortly after Dala's first goal
Dala completed his double from the resulting free-kick with a fine header
Mabululu scored in the second period
Post-Match Reflections: Angola's Gelson Dala scored twice as they reached the Africa Cup of Nations quarterfinals
Namibia's goalkeeper Neblu received a red card in the 17th minute
Namibia looked the most likely to find the net but were left to rue four mad first-half minutes
Miscellaneous Highlights: Angola's 3-0 victory is their biggest ever Cup of Nations finals win
The game took place at Stade de Bouaké in Bouaké, Ivory Coast
The match was attended by 28,663 spectators
